definitions.definition: ( physics , mechanics ) A rotational or twisting effect of a force ; a moment of force , defined for measurement purposes as an equivalent straight line force multiplied by the distance from the axis of rotation (SI unit newton-metre or N·m ; imperial unit pound-foot or lb·ft, not to be confused with the foot pound-force , commonly " foot-pound ", a unit of work or energy)

main_definition: ( physics , mechanics ) A rotational or twisting effect of a force ; a moment of force , defined for measurement purposes as an equivalent straight line force multiplied by the distance from the axis of rotation (SI unit newton-metre or N·m ; imperial unit pound-foot or lb·ft, not to be confused with the foot pound-force , commonly " foot-pound ", a unit of work or energy)

definitions.definition: A tightly braided necklace or collar , often made of metal, worn by various early European peoples.

main_definition: ( historical ) A tightly braided necklace or collar , often made of metal, worn by various early European peoples.
